  "prompt": "Who sings a song titled \"Home\"?",
  "response": "There are several artists who have songs titled \"Home.\" Here are some of the most well-known ones:\n\n1. **Michael Bubl\u00e9**  \n   - Released in 2005 as part of his album *It's Time*.  \n   - A sentimental ballad about longing for home while traveling.  \n\n2. **Edward Sharpe and the Magnetic Zeros**  \n   - Released in 2010 (*Up from Below* album).  \n   - A folk-pop duet between Alex Ebert and Jade Castrinos, with the iconic line, *\"Home is wherever I\u2019m with you.\"*  \n\n3. **Daughtry**  \n   - Rock band fronted by Chris Daughtry; released in 2007 (*Daughtry* album).  \n   - A powerful rock ballad about finding solace in returning home.  \n\n4. **Phillip Phillips**  \n   - Debuted in 2012 as his coronation song after winning *American Idol*.  \n   - Featured in Olympics commercials, with the chorus *\"Hold on, to me as we go...\"*  \n\n5. **Dierks Bentley** (Country)  \n   - Released in 2012 (*Home* album).  \n   - A patriotic country song referencing resilience and national pride.  \n\nIf you have more context (e.g., genre, lyrics, or era), I can help narrow it down!",
